<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12066e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12066e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12066e"> 66(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SP curses W bank of Boyle / Columba born on E bank</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[when SP fell into the river Boyle]</font> He is said to have cursed the western bank of the water. When asked &hellip; why he spared the eastern bank, the Saint replied: &lsquo;A son of life shall arise who, dwelling there hereafter, will like to have good water in this place, and his name shall be Columba.&rsquo; <small> William Canon Fleming, <a name="WFSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WFSP"><cite title="source">The Life of St Patrick: Apostle of Ireland</cite></a> (1905) 112</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
